{
  "stem": "13469.6",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Many of those piles of bodies were inside our camp, kind of thing, so they wouldn't be able to get at those.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But once they got outside, and they probably had far more death than we had, you know, when we had 600 deaths a day, the vast majority of that was in the [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Relatively few of those were in our section of the camp, because the records show that out of the people that went from Westerbork to the star camp-- I think it was 4,000 people-- about half of them came back, survived.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes, we kept on hoping.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We really-- we were boys.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was almost-- I hate to say it-- an adventure story, really that we-- most of the other children, boys like us, they were surviving.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I think that was sort of coming to the end of the Belsen story.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We could hear [INAUDIBLE] the planes more and more.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And in the end, we could actually hear the guns of the Allied forces in the distance-- artillery and all that.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We knew, of course, the Allies had landed a year before in 1944.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we knew that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we knew the Allies were-- You knew that?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, some of the underground people, like the barber and all that sort of thing, would find out all these kind of things.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And those-- we had nothing else to do all day except feed on scraps of rumors.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And anything-- any bits of information that anybody could glean from anywhere would go around the camp like wildfire.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we knew that the Allies were winning and were on their way kind of thing.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we could see it in the air.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
